    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see. it just feels like the debate always focuses on the business struggle. what about the employees? some people argue that higher wages are basically a moral necessity for dignity and reducing poverty. is there a way to look at this where the human impact actually carries as much weight as the economic data, or is the economic cost always the deciding factor?",
